<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Risk: How likely is it to result in death or wipeout?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Perhaps keep track of how many times in a week you are killed by your pet, noting also what sort of support you had when you died.  (Everyone dies on occaision when they solo..)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Cost: How much effort does it take to start and sustain it?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->A relatively small number of xp group logs could give a good idea of this.  You'd need a parser able to track spell casts and, if possible damage taken.  The spells used, how often they are used, and how much each spell costs to use is precisely what is needed.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Potency: How powerful are the charmed mobs?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Logs of DPS dealt and taken is what is mostly relevant.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Applicability: How available are appropriate charmable mobs?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->This is somewhat more difficult than the others in some ways, but at least it doesn't require a log and a parser.  We'd just need to have a list of zones and charmable mobs.  Ideally, though, one would be able to show a series of logs over the course of several weeks or a month, showing how frequently he was able to make use of his charms and in what sorts of situations they were usable.  Some situations may not be suitable for a charmed mob and an inexperienced person might not realize(a plethora of dispelling mobs, for example.)  Encounter tracking might help account for this. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showMessageRange?topicID=422.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showMessageRange?topicID=422.topic&start=41&stop=54>3</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showPrevMessage?topicID=422.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showNextMessage?topicID=422.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=422.topic&index=40><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.threadControl?topicID=422.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicI